! Search & Replace for CodeMirror 6

Full-featured search and replace functionality for the editor.

!! Keyboard Shortcuts

|!Shortcut |!Action |
|`Ctrl+F` / `Cmd+F` |Open search panel |
|`Ctrl+H` / `Cmd+Alt+F` |Open search & replace |
|`F3` / `Ctrl+G` |Find next match |
|`Shift+F3` / `Ctrl+Shift+G` |Find previous match |
|`Ctrl+D` |Select next occurrence |
|`Ctrl+Shift+L` |Select all occurrences |
|`Escape` |Close search panel |
|`Ctrl+G` |Go to line |

!! Features

* ''Find'' - Search for text with match highlighting
* ''Replace'' - Replace current or all matches
* ''Case sensitive'' - Toggle case sensitivity
* ''Regular expressions'' - Use regex patterns
* ''Match whole word'' - Match complete words only
* ''Selection matches'' - Highlight other occurrences of selected text

!! API

The plugin adds these methods to the engine:

* `openSearch()` - Open the search panel
* `closeSearch()` - Close the search panel
* `findNext()` - Jump to next match
* `findPrevious()` - Jump to previous match
* `replaceNext()` - Replace current match
* `replaceAll()` - Replace all matches
* `selectNextOccurrence()` - Add next occurrence to selection
* `selectAllOccurrences()` - Select all occurrences
* `gotoLine()` - Open go to line dialog
* `isSearchOpen()` - Check if search panel is open
